<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-05-26T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-05-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.945/1105a supp.: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Woods</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-26T12:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                        1924—noon</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>81. My telegram No. 80, May 23, 6 p.m.<note n="56" xml:id="d301fn56">Not
                                printed.</note> The President today signed the Immigration Bill, and
                            is issuing a public statement in regard to it which will be telegraphed
                            to you as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>